30/01/2005
MOSCOW, Russia -- Last week's talks between Bulgaria, Greece and Russia cleared the way for going ahead with building the Bourgas-Alexandropoulis oil pipeline, Greek Deputy Energy Minister Georgios Salagoudis told reporters Friday (28 January). He said the negotiations were difficult but ended with the signing of a new co-operation memorandum. Further discussions will be held in Moscow in March. (ANA - 29/01/05; MPA - 28/01/05)
